replies.bodyText:
Thanks for the review! I tried to avoid this complexity at first using a simple
if (OS.getCurrent() != OS.WINDOWS) {
    // POSIX-specific code
}

at first but it didn't work.
I'll give IsDefined.isDarwin() || IsDefined.isLinux() a try but I'm not convinced it will work better since it will be used in a similar way (as a condition in an if block).
Edit: Actually, after reading what @Fold does, I have to retract my previous sentence. It will probably work :)

